params.coin: address of the coin to transfer out.

params.receiver: Destination address for the constituent assets.
params.shares: Number of shares to eject with.

returns.assets: Amount of asset redeemable by the given number of shares.
returns.excessBal: Amount of excess PT or YT redeemable by the given number of shares.
returns.isExcessPTs: Whether the excess token is a YT or PT.

onSponsorWindowOpened(address,uint256).details: We only expect this function to be called by this roller's adapter in the callback triggered within the adapter.openSponsorWindow call.      Assumption: all of this Vault's LP shares will have been exited before this function is called.

previewDeposit(uint256).details: Preview the number of new LP shares that would be minted by joining with the given amount of Target, then use that      as a percentage of the total number of LP shares held in this contract to preview the number of new roller shares.

previewMint(uint256).details: Preview the amount of Target needed to mint the given number of shares by determining how much of      each asset in this contract the given number of shares represent, then conver that all into Target.

params.data: Address to set the param to.
Uint to set the param to.

settle().details: Because the auto-roller is the series sponsor from the Divider's perspective, this.settle is the only entrypoint for athe lastRoller to settle during the series' sponsor window.      More info on the series lifecylce: https://docs.sense.finance/docs/series-lifecycle-detail/#phase-3-settling.

claimRewards(address).notice: Transfer any token not included in the set {asset,yt,pt,space} to the rewards recipient.

eject(uint256,address,address).notice: Quick exit into the constituent assets.

maxRedeem(address).notice: Maximum number of shares the given owner can redeem, given Space pool liquidity constraints and the maxRate guard.

onSponsorWindowOpened(address,uint256).notice: Sponsor a new Series, issue PTs, and migrate liquidity into the new Space pool.

previewDeposit(uint256).notice: The same as convertToShares, except that slippage is considered.

previewRedeem(uint256).notice: The same as convertToAssets, except that slippage is considered.

previewWithdraw(uint256).notice: Amount of shares needed to redeem the given assets, erring on the side of overestimation.         The calculation for previewWithdraw is quite imprecise and expensive, so previewRedeem & redeem         should be favored over previewWithdraw & withdraw.

roll().notice: Roll into the next Series if there isn't an active series and the cooldown period has elapsed.

setParam(bytes32,address).notice: Set address-based admin params, only callable by the owner.

setParam(bytes32,uint256).notice: Set uint-based admin params, only callable by the owner.

settle().notice: Settle the active Series, transfer stake and ifees to the settler, and enter a cooldown phase.

startCooldown().notice: Enter a cooldown phase where users can redeem without slippage. Often this will be initiated by this.settle,         but it can be called externally if the Series was settled externally.

totalAssets().notice: Calculates the total assets of this vault using the current spot prices, with no regard for slippage.
